# UI Text Style Guidelines

## Sentence Case for All UI Text

All user-facing text including titles, button labels, headings, tooltips, and UI labels MUST use sentence case.

### Sentence Case Rules

- **First word capitalized**, rest lowercase
- Capitalize **proper nouns** (product names, specific names, etc.)
- Do NOT use Title Case or ALL CAPS unless it's an acronym

### Examples

✅ **Correct:**
- "Upload files"
- "Create campaign"
- "Add to library"
- "Record session recap"
- "Admin dashboard"
- "What should I do next?"
- "Get help and guidance"
- "Clear all"
- "No campaign selected"

❌ **Incorrect:**
- "Upload Files" (Title Case)
- "Create Campaign" (Title Case)
- "Add To Library" (Title Case)
- "Record Session Recap" (Title Case)
- "ADMIN DASHBOARD" (ALL CAPS)

### Application Areas

This rule applies to:
- Button text and labels
- Modal titles and headings
- Form labels and placeholders
- Dropdown options
- Menu items
- Tooltips
- Alert messages
- Notification text
- Section headings
- Tab labels
- Any other user-visible text

### Exceptions

- **Acronyms**: Keep uppercase (e.g., "API", "URL", "AI")
- **Brand names**: Use official capitalization (e.g., "LoreSmith", "OpenAI")
- **Code/technical terms**: Use appropriate casing when referring to code (e.g., "campaignId")
